Let's get started on managing system and display settings in OpenSUSE.

1
00:00:04,759 --> 00:00:10,214
To change the screen resolution to 1024 x 768 in OpenSUSE:

2
00:00:10,512 --> 00:00:15,238
1. On the OpenSUSE desktop, at the top left corner of screen click Activities.

3
00:00:16,216 --> 00:00:21,274
2. Type settings in the Search box. The Settings icon appears.

4
00:00:22,534 --> 00:00:24,291
3. Click the Settings icon.

5
00:00:24,971 --> 00:00:27,077
The All Settings window appears.

6
00:00:28,404 --> 00:00:30,161
4. Click the Displays icon.

7
00:00:30,344 --> 00:00:32,284
The Displays window appears.

8
00:00:32,698 --> 00:00:35,732
5. Select a display ID to set the resolution.

9
00:00:36,097 --> 00:00:41,237
6. From the Resolution drop-down list, select 1024 x 768.

10
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:42,514
7. Click Apply.

11
00:00:43,211 --> 00:00:45,565
A confirmation message is displayed.

12
00:00:45,615 --> 00:00:47,174
8. Click Keep Changes.

